Core Problem: Google News RSS Limitations
Google News RSS returns a limited, relevance-sorted feed (typically ~20-30 top results), not comprehensive search results. The same articles stay at the top because they're ranked highest, regardless of duration or region parameters. This is why you see the same articles repeatedly.

Strategic Options for Better Results
1. Keyword Expansion & Variations
Your current approach: Single keyword "DJI Dock"

Better approach:

Semantic variations: "DJI Dock", "DJI dock station", "Dock for DJI", "automated drone dock", "drone charging station"
Competitor/adjacent keywords: "drone deployment platform", "drone automation", "autonomous drone systems", "aerial logistics"
Long-tail combinations: "DJI Dock agriculture", "DJI Dock mining", "DJI Dock construction"
Multi-word operators: Search for ("DJI" OR "Flytbase") AND (dock OR deployment OR automation)
Expected impact: 3-5x more unique articles per run

2. Source Expansion (Beyond Google News RSS)
Google News RSS alone won't give you comprehensive coverage. Consider parallel data streams:

Source	Coverage	Latency	Cost	Recommendation
Google News RSS (current)	Broad, generic	1-3 days	Free	Keep as base
NewsAPI.org	70K+ sources, searchable	Real-time	Free tier: 100 req/day	Add immediately
LinkedIn Company Search	Companies, announcements	Real-time	Requires scraping or API	High signal, lower volume
Industry RSS feeds	Specific verticals (drone, ag-tech)	1 day	Free	Drone News, Geospatial Today
Twitter/X API	Real-time mentions	Live	$200/month	Add filters for @flytbase, #drones
Company website monitoring	First-party announcements	Real-time	Custom scraper	Highest quality signal
Quick win: Add NewsAPI — it has better filtering and more sources than Google News.

3. Filtering & Temporal Strategy
Current approach: Fixed time window (14/30/60/90 days) — returns same top results

Better approach:

Rolling window collection: Instead of "last 90 days", run queries with overlapping windows:

"Last 7 days" daily (captures new articles before they age out)
"7-14 days old" weekly (articles that took time to bubble up)
"30-60 days old" monthly (slow-burn stories)
Recency boost: When you have duplicate content, score newer articles higher

Semantic deduplication improvements:

Don't just match URL/title similarity
Cluster articles by topic (use LLM to extract topics, group by topic instead of just title)
Keep the first published version but reference re-reporting across outlets (shows amplification)
4. Search Operator Enrichment
Instead of single keyword, use structured queries:


DJI Dock OR (DJI AND dock AND deployment)
(drone OR unmanned) AND (deployment OR automation) AND NOT toy
DJI AND (agriculture OR mining OR construction OR logistics)
Impact: Captures long-tail articles you'd otherwise miss.

5. Regional Search Optimization
Current limitation: Region parameter (gl/ceid) is edition, not filter

Better approach:

Run separate searches for each language + region:

English (US), English (UK), German, French, Spanish editions
Japanese edition for Asia coverage
Portuguese edition for Brazil
This naturally surfaces region-specific news that doesn't make the global feed

6. Collection Mechanics for Fresh Data
Current approach: Batch collection on-demand with fixed duration

Better approach:

Daily scheduled collection (e.g., 8 AM IST daily)

Small, frequent pulls catch fresh articles before they age off the feed
Combine with D4 cache to avoid re-processing
Incremental collection with state:

Save the timestamp of last collection
Next run: "published after [last_collected_timestamp]"
Prevents re-fetching old content
Trending keyword detection:

Periodically add emerging keywords to the search pool
E.g., if "crop monitoring" suddenly spikes in search volume, add that keyword
7. Source Authority & Deduplication
Once you have more data flowing in:

Weight sources by authority: Reuters > TechCrunch > random blog
Track article propagation: Same news published in NYT then TechCrunch → note it as "amplified"
Cluster duplicate stories: Instead of filtering to one, show "Same story reported by 5 outlets" → signal of importance
